* write a turnin wrapper					:programming:
UI:
  run at local host on local files, use the same syntax:
  turnin --submit [grader] [hw-id] [files ...]
  turnin --list [grader] [hw-id]

  or you can omit the --, I don't like typing --:
  turnin submit [grader] [hw-id] [files ...]
  turnin list [grader] [hw-id]

  allow add alias for grader:
  turnin --alias 345h nwetzler
  turnin alias 371p rekha

  then you can run:
  turnin --list 345h hw1

Implementation:
  search/replace alias with <grader> id
  scp [files] [cs:~/.turnin/<grader>/<hw>/]
  ssh cs "turnin ..."
  
